    <summary>Command-line client for WebSockets, like netcat (or curl) for ws:// with advanced socat-like functions</summary>
    <description>## Description

**websocat** is a command-line client for WebSockets — like netcat or curl for `ws://` and `wss://`, with advanced socat-like functions.

Connect to echo servers, serve WebSocket endpoints, proxy TCP to WebSocket (and back), broadcast messages between clients, pipe stdin/stdout through WebSocket links, and more.

## Features

- Connect to and serve WebSockets from the command line
- Run external programs and bridge stdin/stdout to WebSocket
- Text and binary modes; line- or record-based message conversion
- SOCKS5 proxy support for outbound WebSocket connections
- Auto-reconnect and connection-reuse modes
- Cross-platform; Windows builds included

See the [project wiki](https://github.com/vi/websocat/wiki) and [more examples](https://github.com/vi/websocat/blob/master/moreexamples.md) for usage details.
</description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/vi/websocat/releases/tag/v1.14.1</releaseNotes>
